We have a private repository, and we enabled commit email messages to be sent out to the team. But the email contains raw HTML, and the error message:

{code}
You do not have access to this repository.
{code}

Just thought you all might want to look into this.

-- Josh

Bitbucket — as the sentient being we all know it is — happily sends outs emails from the address »issues-noreply@bitbucket.org« containing this snippet:\\
{{{\\
--- you can reply above this line ---\\
}}}

That&#x27;s not right…
